Here are the lines with potential vulnerabilities:

```
strcpy(card->id, properties->id);
strcpy(card->driver, driver_name);
strcpy(card->shortname, properties->name);
```

To fix this vulnerability, you should use strncpy() or snprintf() instead, which allows you to specify a maximum number of characters to copy. This will prevent buffer overflows by ensuring that the destination buffer is not overrun.

